OL,3,CNo retrial for boy accused of planning
OL,4,Cterror attack
OL,6,FA teenager will not face a retrial
OL,7,Fafter a jury failed to reach a verdict
OL,8,Fon whether he was planning a terror
OL,9,Fattack.
OL,11,FThe 16-year-old boy, who cannot be
OL,12,Fidentified due to his age, was found
OL,13,Fguilty earlier this month of being a
OL,14,Fmember of a proscribed neo-Nazi
OL,15,Forganisation called The Base, as well
OL,16,Fas possessing and publishing terror
OL,17,Fdocuments.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G1/5
